reviewText: I'm a huge fan of Katt! I definitely find it interesting to be able to get inside the head of such a brilliant comedian. You learn that he has 8 kids (7 of whom are adopted). Can you imagine that household?!? I'm sure that's pure comedy in its own right.Some things I found interesting on this DVD were the TV appearance clips and some old unreleased stand up footage.I enjoyed the DVD and think it's a great gift for any Katt fanatics!

reviewText: I Got This DVD Last Night At The Store, When I First Got It I Thought It Was Some New Stand Up But Once I Watched I Realized It Was A Documentary With Little Clips From Pervious DVD's Mixed Into It. Unforutently Katt Retired. It Was A Nice Documentry No Doubt And Found Out Alot Of Stuff About Katt That I Did Not Know. Reccomend If You Want To Know More About Katt, Do Not Reccomend If Your Looking For A Stand Up Special.EDIT: If You Have the Katt Pack, The Bonus Disc Is A Shortened Version Of This.
